body:
Hello, im using PowerShell.SDK and PowerShell.Commands.Diagnostics to call a powershell script which is supposed to reboot a webapp on Azure.
However, I cannot get it to load AzureRM.Websites module to perform the task.


# Steps to reproduce

```
InitialSessionState initialState = InitialSessionState.CreateDefault();
            initialState.ImportPSModule(new string[]
            {
                "PATH_TO_AzureRM.psm1" //tried also AzureRM.Websites or AzureRM.psd1
});
Runspace runspace = RunspaceFactory.CreateRunspace(initialState);
            runspace.Open();
PowerShell powerShellInstance = PowerShell.Create();
            powerShellInstance.Runspace = runspace;

            string initializationScript = "Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope Process -ExecutionPolicy Unrestricted";
            powerShellInstance.AddScript(initializationScript);
            powerShellInstance.Invoke();

            //Here I use AddScript/Invoke/AddCommand/Invoke to launch a powershell script which try to call the Restart-AzureRmWebApp method.
```

# Expected behavior

```
The Restart-AzureRmWebApp is recognized and executed
```

# Actual behavior

```
Exception Type: System.Management.Automation.CommandNotFoundException
Exception Message: The term 'Restart-AzureRmWebApp' is not recognized as the name of a cmdlet, function, script file, or operable program.
```


Is there something im missing ?
It seems like the ImportPSModule does nothing
